# PsychicHttp → ESPAsyncWebServer Migration Rules

## Library Reference
- Target: ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer v3.10.0 (https://github.com/ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer)
- Docs: https://esp32async.github.io/ESPAsyncWebServer
- JSON support via `#include <AsyncJson.h>` and ArduinoJson v7

## Core Type Mapping

| PsychicHttp | ESPAsyncWebServer | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `PsychicHttpServer` | `AsyncWebServer` | Constructor takes port: `AsyncWebServer server(80)` |
| `PsychicHttpServer*` | `AsyncWebServer*` | Pointer usage stays the same |
| `PsychicRequest*` | `AsyncWebServerRequest*` | |
| `PsychicResponse` | `AsyncWebServerResponse*` | Created via `request->beginResponse(...)` |
| `PsychicJsonResponse` | `AsyncJsonResponse*` | `new AsyncJsonResponse()`, then `request->send(response)` |
| `PsychicFileResponse` | N/A | Use `request->send(FS, path, contentType)` |
| `PsychicWebHandler` | N/A | Handlers are lambdas directly |
| `PsychicWebSocketHandler` | `AsyncWebSocket` | Constructor takes path: `AsyncWebSocket ws("/ws")` |
| `PsychicWebSocketClient*` | `AsyncWebSocketClient*` | Different API for id/sending |
| `PsychicWebSocketRequest*` | N/A | Data comes via `onEvent` callback |
| `PsychicUploadHandler` | N/A | Upload is 3rd param of `server.on()` |
| `PsychicRequestFilterFunction` | `AsyncWebHandler::FilterFunction` or custom | |
| `PsychicHttpRequestCallback` | `ArRequestHandlerFunction` | Signature: `void(AsyncWebServerRequest*)` |
| `PsychicJsonRequestCallback` | Custom typedef needed | Signature: `void(AsyncWebServerRequest*, JsonVariant&)` |

## Critical API Differences

### Return types
- PsychicHttp handlers return `esp_err_t` → AsyncWebServer handlers return `void`
- Remove ALL `return ESP_OK`, `return response.send()`, `return request->reply()`
- Instead: call `request->send(...)` and just `return;`

### Server initialization
```cpp
// OLD:
_server->config.max_uri_handlers = _numberEndpoints;
_server->listen(80);

// NEW:
// Port set in constructor: AsyncWebServer server(80);
_server->begin();
```

### Simple response
```cpp
// OLD:
return request->reply(200);
return request->reply(401);

// NEW:
request->send(200);
return;
// or just: request->send(401);
```

### Response with headers
```cpp
// OLD:
PsychicResponse response(request);
response.setCode(200);
response.setContentType(contentType.c_str());
response.addHeader("Content-Encoding", "gzip");
response.addHeader("Cache-Control", "public, immutable, max-age=31536000");
response.setContent(content, len);
return response.send();

// NEW:
AsyncWebServerResponse *response = request->beginResponse(200, contentType, content, len);
response->addHeader("Content-Encoding", "gzip");
response->addHeader("Cache-Control", "public, immutable, max-age=31536000");
request->send(response);
```

### JSON response
```cpp
// OLD:
PsychicJsonResponse response = PsychicJsonResponse(request, false);
JsonObject root = response.getRoot();
root["key"] = "value";
return response.send();

// NEW:
AsyncJsonResponse *response = new AsyncJsonResponse();
JsonObject root = response->getRoot();
root["key"] = "value";
response->setLength();
request->send(response);
```

### JSON request handler (POST with body)
```cpp
// OLD:
_server->on(path, HTTP_POST, callback);
// where callback is PsychicJsonRequestCallback = std::function<esp_err_t(PsychicRequest*, JsonVariant&)>

// NEW:
AsyncCallbackJsonWebHandler *handler = new AsyncCallbackJsonWebHandler(path,
    [](AsyncWebServerRequest *request, JsonVariant &json) {
        // handle json...
        request->send(200);
    });
_server->addHandler(handler);
```

### File response
```cpp
// OLD:
PsychicFileResponse response(request, ESPFS, "/www/index.html", "text/html");
return response.send();

// NEW:
request->send(ESPFS, "/www/index.html", "text/html");
```

### Endpoint registration
```cpp
// OLD:
_server->on(path, HTTP_GET, handler);  // handler is PsychicWebHandler* or callback

// NEW:
_server->on(path, HTTP_GET, handler);  // handler is ArRequestHandlerFunction (lambda)
```

### File upload
```cpp
// OLD:
PsychicUploadHandler *uploadHandler = new PsychicUploadHandler();
uploadHandler->onUpload(handleUploadFn);
uploadHandler->onRequest(handleCompleteFn);
_server->on(path, HTTP_POST, uploadHandler);

// NEW:
_server->on(path, HTTP_POST,
    [this](AsyncWebServerRequest *request) { uploadComplete(request); },
    [this](AsyncWebServerRequest *request, String filename, size_t index,
           uint8_t *data, size_t len, bool final) {
        handleUpload(request, filename, index, data, len, final);
    });
// Note: upload handler signature differs - index is size_t, not uint64_t
```

### Static file serving
```cpp
// OLD and NEW are similar:
_server->serveStatic("/path/", FS, "/dir/");
```

### Not found handler
```cpp
// OLD:
_server->onNotFound([](PsychicRequest *request) { ... return ...; });

// NEW:
_server->onNotFound([](AsyncWebServerRequest *request) { ... });
```

### Default headers / CORS
```cpp
// OLD:
DefaultHeaders::Instance().addHeader("Access-Control-Allow-Origin", CORS_ORIGIN);

// NEW:
DefaultHeaders::Instance().addHeader("Access-Control-Allow-Origin", CORS_ORIGIN);
// Same API!
```

## WebSocket Migration

### Handler setup
```cpp
// OLD:
PsychicWebSocketHandler _socket;
_socket.setFilter(filterFn);
_socket.onOpen(openFn);
_socket.onClose(closeFn);
_socket.onFrame(frameFn);
_server->on(path, &_socket);

// NEW:
AsyncWebSocket _socket("/ws/path");  // path in constructor
_socket.onEvent([this](AsyncWebSocket *server, AsyncWebSocketClient *client,
                       AwsEventType type, void *arg, uint8_t *data, size_t len) {
    switch (type) {
        case WS_EVT_CONNECT: onWSOpen(client); break;
        case WS_EVT_DISCONNECT: onWSClose(client); break;
        case WS_EVT_DATA: {
            AwsFrameInfo *info = (AwsFrameInfo*)arg;
            if (info->final && info->index == 0 && info->len == len) {
                onWSFrame(client, info, data, len);
            }
            break;
        }
    }
});
_server->addHandler(&_socket);
```

### Client identification
```cpp
// OLD:
client->socket()       // int fd
client->remoteIP()     // IPAddress

// NEW:
client->id()           // uint32_t
client->remoteIP()     // IPAddress (same)
```

### Sending messages
```cpp
// OLD:
client->sendMessage(buffer.c_str());
client->sendMessage(HTTPD_WS_TYPE_TEXT, output, len);
client->sendMessage(HTTPD_WS_TYPE_BINARY, output, len);
_socket.sendAll(buffer.c_str());

// NEW:
client->text(buffer.c_str());
client->text(output, len);
client->binary(output, len);
_socket.textAll(buffer.c_str());
_socket.binaryAll(output, len);
```

### Getting clients
```cpp
// OLD:
_socket.getClient(clientId)         // PsychicWebSocketClient*
_socket.getClientList()             // std::list<PsychicWebSocketClient*>
_server->getClientList()            // for all server clients

// NEW:
_socket.client(clientId)            // AsyncWebSocketClient*
_socket.getClients()                // LinkedList<AsyncWebSocketClient*>
_socket.count()                     // number of connected clients
```

### Frame data access
```cpp
// OLD:
frame->type      // httpd_ws_type_t (HTTPD_WS_TYPE_TEXT, HTTPD_WS_TYPE_BINARY)
frame->payload   // uint8_t*
frame->len       // size_t

// NEW:
// Data comes via onEvent callback:
AwsFrameInfo *info = (AwsFrameInfo*)arg;
info->opcode     // WS_TEXT or WS_BINARY
data             // uint8_t* (parameter)
len              // size_t (parameter)
info->final      // bool - is this the final frame?
info->index      // offset in message
info->len        // total frame length
```

## Security wrapper pattern adaptation

### New callback typedefs needed
```cpp
typedef std::function<void(AsyncWebServerRequest *request)> AsyncHttpRequestCallback;
typedef std::function<void(AsyncWebServerRequest *request, JsonVariant &json)> AsyncJsonRequestCallback;
typedef std::function<bool(AsyncWebServerRequest *request)> AsyncRequestFilterFunction;
```

### wrapRequest pattern
```cpp
// OLD:
PsychicHttpRequestCallback wrapRequest(PsychicHttpRequestCallback onRequest, AuthenticationPredicate predicate) {
    return [this, onRequest, predicate](PsychicRequest *request) {
        Authentication authentication = authenticateRequest(request);
        if (!predicate(authentication)) { return request->reply(401); }
        return onRequest(request);
    };
}

// NEW:
AsyncHttpRequestCallback wrapRequest(AsyncHttpRequestCallback onRequest, AuthenticationPredicate predicate) {
    return [this, onRequest, predicate](AsyncWebServerRequest *request) {
        Authentication authentication = authenticateRequest(request);
        if (!predicate(authentication)) { request->send(401); return; }
        onRequest(request);
    };
}
```

## Request API differences
```cpp
// OLD:
request->method()                    // http_method enum
request->uri()                       // String
request->host()                      // String
request->contentLength()             // size_t
request->hasHeader("name")           // bool
request->header("name")              // String
request->hasParam("name")            // bool
request->getParam("name")->value()   // String
request->loadParams()                // void - load query params
request->_tempObject                 // void* for user data

// NEW:
request->method()                    // WebRequestMethod enum
request->url()                       // String (not uri!)
request->host()                      // String
request->contentLength()             // size_t
request->hasHeader("name")           // bool
request->getHeader("name")->value()  // String (not header()!)
request->hasParam("name")            // bool
request->getParam("name")->value()   // String
// No loadParams needed
request->_tempObject                 // void* (same)
```

## Important notes
- PsychicMqttClient depends on PsychicHttp. It will pull its own PsychicHttp. Keep it as-is for now; MQTT migration is out of scope.
- `_server->maxUploadSize` does not exist in AsyncWebServer. Size validation must be done in the upload handler.
- `_server->defaultEndpoint->setHandler(handler)` → use `_server->onNotFound(handler)` instead.
- `_server->config.max_uri_handlers` → not needed, AsyncWebServer handlers are dynamic.
- AsyncWebServer response lifecycle: `new AsyncJsonResponse()` is freed by the framework after sending.
- `PsychicWebHandler` does not exist in AsyncWebServer; use lambdas directly.
